messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- Full HTTP request path:
  /cms/user

- All HTTP methods acceptable:
  False

- HEAD:
  False

- POST:
  False

- OPTIONS:
  False

- TRACE:
  False

- GET:
  False

- PUT:
  True

- DELETE:
  False

- PATCH:
  False

Explanation:
- The handler is defined in app/api/cms/user.py with @user_api.route("", methods=["PUT"]) named update. The route's rule is the empty string ("") on the user blueprint.
- The user blueprint is registered in app/api/cms/__init__.py with url_prefix="/user".
- The cms blueprint (which contains the user blueprint) is registered on the application in app/__init__.py with url_prefix="/cms".
- Concatenating the prefixes and the empty rule yields the full path /cms/user.
- The route decorator explicitly sets methods=["PUT"], so only PUT is accepted. There is no code that makes "all methods" acceptable, nor are other HTTP methods (HEAD, POST, OPTIONS, TRACE, GET, DELETE, PATCH) explicitly allowed in this handler; therefore they are reported as not acceptable based on the code.
